                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="71749" author="pjones" created="Mon, 18 Nov 2013 05:10:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Landed for 2.4.2&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65579" author="yujian" created="Tue, 3 Sep 2013 08:06:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch for Lustre b2_4 branch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/7529&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/7529&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65577" author="yujian" created="Tue, 3 Sep 2013 07:34:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The patch on master branch is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;commit f5491211ed7251a45e4e6916539cd2a2ab5e6038
Author: Fan Yong &amp;lt;yong.fan@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;
Date:   Sun May 19 12:26:37 2013 +0800

    LU-2915 lfsck: LFSCK 1.5 technical debts (2)
    
    This patch resolves some LFSCK 1.5 technical debts, including:
    1) LFSCK does NOT hold spin_lock when call dt iteration API(s).
    2) Remove the hack of using dt_it_ops::put() method for events
       notification to low layer otable-based iteration.
    
    Test-Parameters: testlist=sanity-scrub,sanity-lfsck
    Signed-off-by: Fan Yong &amp;lt;fan.yong@intel.com&amp;gt;
    Change-Id: Ie16161370ac218860a74b23d853c4c378adce4ec
    Reviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/6343
    Tested-by: Hudson
    Tested-by: Maloo &amp;lt;whamcloud.maloo@gmail.com&amp;gt;
    Reviewed-by: Alex Zhuravlev &amp;lt;alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com&amp;gt;
    Reviewed-by: Andreas Dilger &amp;lt;andreas.dilger@intel.com&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;diff --git a/lustre/tests/sanity-scrub.sh b/lustre/tests/sanity-scrub.sh
&amp;lt;~snip~&amp;gt;
+# test_10b is obsolete, it will be coverded by related sanity-lfsck tests.
 test_10b() {
        scrub_prep 0
        mds_backup_restore || error &quot;(1) Fail to backup/restore!&quot;
@@ -742,7 +743,7 @@ test_10b() {
        FLAGS=$($SHOW_SCRUB | awk &apos;/^flags/ { print $2 }&apos;)
        [ -z &quot;$FLAGS&quot; ] || error &quot;(14) Expect empty flags, but got &apos;$FLAGS&apos;&quot;
 }
-run_test 10b &quot;non-stopped OI scrub should auto restarts after MDS remount (2)&quot;
+#run_test 10b &quot;non-stopped OI scrub should auto restarts after MDS remount (2)&quot;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the suggestion from Nasf, we only need add Lustre version check code into sanity-scrub test 10b on Lustre b2_4 branch to resolve the interop failure. I&apos;ll upload the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65429" author="yujian" created="Fri, 30 Aug 2013 12:19:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi nasf,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Do you know which patch on master branch fixed this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="65382" author="jlevi" created="Thu, 29 Aug 2013 16:59:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Oleg believes there is a fix in 2.5 for this that just needs to be ported to 2.4.&lt;br/&gt;
Could you please take a look at this?&lt;br/&gt;
Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
